	Crowe Music    
	 Melbourne, Aug. 7 (PTI): Actor Russell Crowe is all set to take the place of actor Heath Ledger in the Australian film Dirt Music.      
	Ledger, who passed away in 2008, had originally signed up to star in the film adaptation of Tim Wintons novel alongside Rachel Weisz, but he later quit the production in order to tackle the role of The Joker in The Dark Knight.      
	 The project ground to a halt as producers searched for a replacement for Ledger, and now director Phillip Noyce has finally confirmed that the film will be shot with Crowe in the lead role, reports The Daily Telegraph.    
	Susan kids    
	 London (PTI): Actress Susan Sarandon has lend a supporting hand to a new campaign that strives to wipe out child trafficking from the face of the planet. Sarandon, 63, is backing a petition launched by the Somaly Mam Foundation, anti-child trafficking charity ECPAT-USA, and cosmetics chain The Body Shop, reports the Daily Star.    
	Justin gay    
	 Los Angeles (PTI): Grammy-award-winning musician Justin Timberlake is all set to turn gay for an animated character. Timberlake, 29, is lending his vocal talents to a gay character on his animated series The Cleveland Show, reports Us magazine. Timberlakes character is called Paul.                                                                                                                                                       
